data.enText: to laugh at sb and make jokes about them, either in a friendly way or in order to annoy or embarrass them

data.chText: 别不高兴，我只是在逗你玩。
data.enText: Don't get upset─I was only teasing.

data.chText: 过去别人总拿我的名字开玩笑。
data.enText: I used to get teased about my name.

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+直接引语

data.enText: to annoy an animal, especially by touching it, pulling its tail, etc.
to make sb sexually excited, especially when you do not intend to have sex with them
to pull sth gently apart into separate pieces
to remove knots from hair, wool, etc. by gently pulling or brushing it

data.chText: 探讨；深入研究；梳理清楚
data.enText: to spend time trying to find out information or the meaning of sth, especially when this is complicated or difficult

data.chText: 老师帮助他们弄清楚那首诗的含义。
data.enText: The teacher helped them tease out the meaning of the poem.

data.chText: 爱戏弄人的人；逗弄者；取笑者
data.enText: a person who likes to play tricks and jokes on other people, especially by telling them sth that is not true or by not telling them sth that they want to know
an act that is intended as a trick or joke

data.chText: 卖弄风骚的人；勾引人者
data.enText: a person who pretends to be attracted to sb, makes them sexually excited and then refuses to have sex with them

ex.chText: 别紧张，我只是开玩笑而已。
这个问题可不能拿来开玩笑。
ex.enText: This is not a matter to joke about.

ex.chText: 那位女演员和记者们开起了玩笑。
他们拿婚姻问题逗比尔。
ex.enText: They bantered with Bill on the subject of marriage.

ex.chText: 别生气，我只不过是开玩笑。
ex.enText: Don't get mad, I was only kidding.

ex.chText: 他说他在与一位女演员谈恋爱，我还以为他在开玩笑呢。
ex.enText: I thought he was kidding when he said he was going out with an actress.

synonyms.bx: 指通过告诉某人非真实的情况来戏弄他，通常用进行时。

ex.chText: 取笑残疾人是不礼貌的。
ex.enText: It's not polite to tease the disabled.

ex.chText: 他们过去常常取笑她的头发。
ex.enText: They used to tease her about her hair.

tr: the act of harassing someone playfully or maliciously (especially by ridicule)
example: his ribbing was gentle but persistent

tr: a seductive woman who uses her sex appeal to exploit men
someone given to teasing (as by mocking or stirring curiosity)
ruffle (one's hair) by combing the ends towards the scalp, for a full effect
harass with persistent criticism or carping
example: The children teased the new teacher
Don't ride me so hard over my failure
His fellow workers razzed him when he wore a jacket and tie

tr: mock or make fun of playfully
example: the flirting man teased the young woman

tr: disentangle and raise the fibers of

example: The children teased the boy because of his stammer

tr: to arouse hope, desire, or curiosity without satisfying them
example: The advertisement is intended to tease the customers
She has a way of teasing men with her flirtatious behavior

value.def: To tease someone means to laugh at them or make jokes about them in order to embarrass, annoy, or upset them.

example.ex: He told her how the boys in East Poldown had set on him, teasing him...
example.tran: 他告诉她东波尔顿的男孩们是如何攻击他、嘲笑他的。

example.ex: He teased me mercilessly about going Hollywood...
example.tran: 他毫不留情地嘲笑我想去好莱坞。

example.ex: 'You must be expecting a young man,' she teased.
example.tran: “你一定是在等哪位小伙子吧，”她揶揄道。

example.ex: Calling her by her real name had always been one of his teases.
example.tran: 他一直把称呼她的真名当作一种取乐。

example.ex: She tolerated the teasing, until the fourth grade.
example.tran: 她忍受着别人的嘲笑，一直忍到四年级。

value.def: If you refer to someone as a tease, you mean that they like laughing at people or making jokes about them.

example.tran: 我弟弟太喜欢戏弄人了。

example.ex: The best way to deal with a tease is to ignore him.
example.tran: 对付爱捉弄人的人的最佳方法就是不搭理他。

value.tran: 爱开玩笑的人;爱戏弄别人的人

value.def: If you say that someone is teasing, you mean that they are pretending to offer you something that you want, especially sex, but then not giving it to you.

example.ex: I thought she was teasing, playing the innocent, but looking back, I'm not so sure...
example.tran: 我当时以为她是在勾引我，装纯情，不过现在回想起来，我又说不准了。

example.ex: When did you last flirt with him or tease him?
example.tran: 你上次和他调情或挑逗他是什么时候？

value.def: If you refer to someone as a tease, you mean that they pretend to offer someone what they want, especially sex, but then do not give it to them.

example.ex: Later she heard he had told one of her friends she was a tease.
example.tran: 后来，她听说他告诉她的一个朋友，说她是狐狸精。

value.tran: (尤指性方面)戏弄别人的人，挑逗别人的人，卖弄风情的人
